[The first article does not tell us, but
hopefully the exposed people are being treated
with post-exposure prophylaxis. Neither does this
article tell us what strain of rabies the cat
had. In addition, it would seem prudent to
recommend that owners be reminded to have their pets vaccinated.

The 2nd article does not tell us the strain of
strain of rabies either. Likewise, the condition
of the dog, or whether or not it was vaccinated
against the disease is not conveyed here. Likely
the dog is quarantined but it is not stated.
Again, it would be prudent to remind animal
owners to get their pets vaccinated against rabies. ­ Mod.TG
